tspan.tspan: File names are used for sample names.
absorbance_path can be a directory or a file
containing absorption data. Multiple files are
combined into one table. Sample names can be set
in columns or in the file name (when column
a propper naming sceme is crucial for a functioning
→ must not start with a number
Some functions offer the optional (!) possibility to supply
data (dilution factor, Raman area, photometer cuvette
length) as single column data frames (e.g. table read by
read.table). The row names are sample names.

text.tspan: the keyword wavelength is searched for and considered
to be in the first row of the header
